humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: According to the pathology report, multiple left axillary sentinel lymph nodes (5) and left axillary lymph nodes (25) were excised and assessed. No metastatic carcinoma was found in any of these lymph nodes. Therefore, based on New Rule 11, the N stage is N0, as all assessed lymph nodes are negative for metastatic carcinoma.

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The patient has metastatic adenocarcinoma in the left breast intramammary lymph node, as indicated in the report. However, all other examined lymph nodes, including 5 sentinel lymph nodes and 2 highest nodes in the left axillary region, are negative for tumor. Therefore, based on the information provided, the patient's pathologic N stage is N1.
